   On June 9, Mount Sinabung in North Sumatra, Indonesia, erupted and sent a
   huge plume of thick ash into the sky.

Mount Sinabung on Indonesia’s Sumatra island recently erupted, sending a
     massive column of ash and smoke into the air and coating local villages
     in debris.

Sinabung volcano Sumatra Indonesia 🇮🇩 on sunday the 9th June 2019 at
     04:28.
